<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id624ea753-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1303"><num value="1303">§ 1303.</num><heading> Habeas corpus</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The privilege of the writ of habeas corpus shall be available to any person, in a court of the United States, to test the legality of his detention by order of an Indian tribe.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id624ea754-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/284/tII/s203">Pub. L. 90–284, title II, § 203</ref>, <date date="1968-04-11">Apr. 11, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/78">82 Stat. 78</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
